Widmer Sale, Genève, Moos [?] 30-X-1937 Martin van Cleve, N° 12-Intérieur de ferme. Attestation Friedländer. Mentionné, Frimmel, Gemäldekunde 1905, N° 6, p. 117, repr. p. 116, panneau, 78,5 x 58,5 cm. The composition is different from the Visit to the Farm, but some details are similar. Is this the same composition as that sold at Christie's 1954, as Brueghel?; [verso] Frimmel's note refers to the followers. The same composition, but 76x137 cm. Fleischner Sale, Vienna [...]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
